node.title: Defence Minister says China 'sees us as a tributary state' that should submit to its power
node.description: The Defence Minister says China sees Australia and other countries in the region as subordinate states that should be submissive to it, as he warns Beijing would quickly dominate Asia if it succeeds in invading Taiwan.

node.title: Chinese official gets Interpol post despite opposition from Australian MPs
node.description: Interpol's member countries vote to appoint a Chinese public security official to the international law enforcement body's executive committee, despite objections from a group of Australian MPs and international human rights organisations.

node.title: Fast bowlers are almost never Test captains, and it's for a reason you might not suspect
node.description: Pat Cummins has become the first Australian fast bowler in history to earn a full-time gig as Test captain. So why are quicks rarely picked for leadership? Simon Smale explains.

node.title: Before an impulse buy on Black Friday, check the fine print on your so-called 'deal', consumer groups warn
node.description: Black Friday and Cyber Monday are now firmly entrenched in the Australian sales calendar, rivalling more traditional sale events such as Boxing Day, but this November may not be the time to get the best deal.

node.title: 'Once-in-a-lifetime opportunity': Mothers' emotional plea for change as defence and veteran suicide royal commission begins
node.description: A mother whose army veteran son took his own life calls for reform at the start of the long-awaited Royal Commission into Defence and Veteran Suicide.

node.title: Queuing overnight for smartphones or concert tickets? Here, they camp out for art
node.description: Instead of pushing and shoving to secure the latest device or sale item this Black Friday, these people camped out for a chance to choose a piece of art.

node.title: Euthanasia bill passes lower house of NSW Parliament
node.description: Independent MP Alex Greenwich's voluntary assisted dying bill passes the lower house of Parliament 52 votes to 32.

node.title: Covid-19: Police and Defence Force will be required to be vaccinated
node.description: NZ police and Defence Force workers will be required to be vaccinated as part of the Covid-19 traffic light system.

node.title: Victoria records 1362 new local Covid-19 cases, seven deaths
node.description: Victoria has recorded 1362 new local Covid-19 cases and seven deaths as the state enjoys a rolling back of border restrictions.

node.title: Ferry repairs force changes to thousands of summer bookings
node.description: Sailing times for up to 10,000 summer holiday travellers are being changed because of Cook Strait ferry cancellations.

node.title: Woman Torches Gaming Machine, Gets Shot by Fellow Player, Police Say
node.description: Most forms of gambling are illegal in Texas—unlike its neighboring states—but the illegal gambling industry generates over $2 billion annually within the state.

node.title: Prime Minister says he's 'not afraid' of Liberal MP rebellions on government votes
node.description: The Liberal Party is not a group of "warm bodies and drones" for the Prime Minister to push around, Scott Morrison says, as he responds to a week of government backbenchers in both houses voting against him.

node.title: Pat Cummins named as new Australian men's Test cricket captain
node.description: Cricket Australia confirms it has chosen Pat Cummins to lead Australia in the upcoming Ashes series, naming the paceman as the new Test skipper.

node.title: Sports sector's mixed reaction to pending border changes
node.description: There's a mixed mood among the New Zealand elite sports community as athletes and officials continue to digest the major border changes announced by the government.

node.title: Collins and Bridges should consider leaving Parliament - Christopher Finlayson
node.description: Former senior National MPs are weighing in amid chaos and turmoil in the party with calls for Judith Collins, Simon Bridges and party president Peter Goodfellow to stand aside. Audio

node.title: 'A sort of healer' - Artist Robert Ellis dead at 92
node.description: New Zealand artist Robert Ellis died this week at the age of 92, leaving behind a prominent body of artwork that brought together pakeha and Māori influences. Audio
